Durban - The defence in the trial against the man who allegedly caused the car crash that killed Top Billing presenter Simba Mhere and a friend argued that a mechanical failure was the cause of the crash.Defence witness IBF Investigations chief reconstruction expert, Stanley Bezuidenhout, showed an image he told the court demonstrated that Preshalin Naidoo s vehicle was in an abnormal state when the crash occurred. It showed there was a nut missing on the vehicle, which could have caused a mechanical failure in the steering wheel. The case was postponed to March 6 in the Randburg Magistrates Court.Sunday Tribune